msgid "<div class=\"text-center\">\n"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:69
msgid "Things to be aware of"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:71
msgid ""
"![Computer with squashed banana wallpaper](/linux/Computer-Screen-"
"_ripe_banana.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:72
msgid "</div>\n"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:74
msgid ""
"**KDE Linux is Alpha software.** Do not install it on your non-technical "
"uncle’s computer or across the accounting department at work. There are "
"[multiple known issues](https://community.kde.org/KDE_Linux#Current_state) "
"(make sure nothing in there is a deal-breaker for you). KDE Linux has only "
"received limited testing so far, and there will be regressions and bad "
"builds you’ll have to roll back. Data loss has not been experienced yet, but"
" anything is possible. Deploy a robust backup system. Expect some "
"adventures."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:75
msgid ""
"**Opportunities for customizing the base OS are extremely limited.** As an "
"“immutable base” operating system, KDE Linux deliberately limits system-"
"level customization to preserve reliability. Don’t go starting and stopping "
"Systemd services except to debug or fix reported bugs. Don’t try hacks to "
"customize your Plymouth splash screen or SDDM theme."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:76
msgid ""
"**The experience of using an older NVIDIA GPU is rough.** [Manual "
"setup](/docs/pre-turing-nvidia) is currently required for anything older "
"than an NVIDIA GTX 1630 to even work at all, and they are essentially "
"untested. Here be dragons. You’ve been warned."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:77
msgid ""
"**Do not report bugs for yesterday’s version.** That’s right: currently KDE "
"Linux is being updated daily. If you think you found a bug… update the whole"
" system first! If the bug is still there, go ahead and report it. {{< "
"/section >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:88
msgid "General information"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:90
msgid "How is this free? What’s the catch?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:91
msgid ""
"No catch! KDE Linux is a volunteer-run project with financial support from "
"[KDE e.V.](https://ev.kde.org) There are no ads, and it does not transmit or"
" sell your personal information."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:94
msgid "Who is KDE Linux for?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:95
msgid ""
"At the moment, only the Testing edition is available. The more these "
"sentences describe you, the happier you’ll be using it:"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:97
msgid "You’re a KDE fan"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:98
msgid ""
"You get excited about modern technology like Systemd, immutable OSs, "
"containerized apps, and Btrfs"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:99
msgid "You want to participate in KDE’s QA process and find issues early"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:100
msgid "You’re a KDE Plasma developer"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:101
msgid "You don’t have an NVIDIA GPU that’s over 6 years old"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:104
msgid "How do I install apps?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:105
msgid ""
"The *Discover* app is your gateway to the world of Linux apps. Open it and "
"browse through what’s available, or search for something specific."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:108
msgid "How do I update the system?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:109
msgid ""
"KDE Linux will notify you when updates are available. Just click the "
"notification about updates to launch *Discover* and see what’s available. "
"Click “Update All” when you’re ready to update."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:111
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can update the system using `updatectl update` in a "
"terminal window."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:113
msgid ""
"The next time you restart the system, the update will be instantly applied."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:116
msgid ""
"How can I roll back to an older version if there’s a problem after updating?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:117
msgid ""
"When you turn on the computer, a list of KDE Linux versions will be shown "
"for a few seconds. While this list is visible, use the Down arrow key to "
"select an older version, and then press Enter."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:120
msgid "Where can I report issues and get help?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:121
msgid "Since KDE Linux is pre-alpha, please report issues you encounter!"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:123
msgid ""
"Report issues in the KDE Linux operating system itself (i.e. OS design, "
"integration, system services, etc.) on "
"[invent.kde.org](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/issues/), and "
"ignore the scary red banner at the top of the page."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:124
msgid ""
"Report issues in KDE Plasma or any KDE apps on "
"[bugs.kde.org](https://bugs.kde.org/)."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:125
msgid ""
"Get help with something that’s not necessarily a bug on "
"[discuss.kde.org](https://discuss.kde.org/c/help/6), and tag your post with "
"“kde-linux”. {{< /section >}}"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:132
msgid "Information for techies"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:134
msgid "Is this “The KDE OS”?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:135
msgid ""
"Yes! KDE Linux is the KDE community’s idea of a “reference implementation” "
"OS with Plasma and KDE apps."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:137
msgid ""
"Though it’s designed to be suitable for general uses, KDE Linux may be less "
"optimized and optimizable for specific uses compared to other operating "
"systems. KDE Linux is not an attempt to discourage people from using them, "
"but rather to raise the quality level for all KDE-centric operating systems."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:140
msgid "What kind of base technology does KDE Linux use?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:141
msgid ""
"KDE Linux is an “immutable base OS” Linux distro created using Arch Linux "
"packages, but it should not be considered an “Arch-based distro”; Arch is "
"simply a means to an end, and KDE Linux doesn’t even ship with the `pacman` "
"package manager."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:143
msgid ""
"KDE Linux leans on Systemd for a great deal of functionality. Updates are "
"atomic and image-based, with the last 5 OS images cached on disk. Only the "
"Wayland session is supported. Apps primarily come from Flatpak."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:145
msgid ""
"Learn more about [KDE Linux’s "
"architecture](https://community.kde.org/KDE_Linux/Background_information#Architecture)."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:148
msgid "How can I install more specialized software not available in Discover?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:149
msgid ""
"As an “immutable base” operating system, KDE Linux does not include a "
"traditional package manager that can modify the base OS. However, there are "
"still multiple options for getting software not available in Discover:"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:151
msgid ""
"*Distrobox* and *Toolbox* come pre-installed, and can install traditional "
"packages from the Linux distro of your choice into containers in your home "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:152
msgid ""
"[*Nix*](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nix_(package_manager)) can also be "
"installed to provide a large repository of software."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:153
msgid ""
"You can compile software yourself, either into your home directory or on top"
" of the base system using `systemd-sysext`."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:154
msgid "AppImage apps downloaded from the internet work too."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:156
msgid ""
"Learn more about [installing additional software](/docs/more-software)."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:159
msgid "What’s the deal with older NVIDIA GPUs?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:160
msgid ""
"NVIDIA GPUs using an architecture older than Turing (this means anything "
"older than GTX 1630) require NVIDIA’s proprietary kernel modules. These "
"modules cannot be loaded at runtime because the base OS is immutable, and "
"pre-installing them appears to be in a [legal gray "
"area](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux_kernel#Loadable_kernel_modules). "
"To be safe, KDE Linux doesn’t include them."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:162
msgid ""
"Newer NVIDIA GPUs (Turing/GTX 1630 and newer) can use NVIDIA’s open kernel "
"modules which are redistributable with the base OS in a legally clear "
"manner, so KDE Linux pre-installs them. Necessary NVIDIA userspace drivers "
"and utilities are also pre-installed, so these GPUs should work without "
"drama."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:164
msgid ""
"Older NVIDIA GPUs *should* work with the less-performant Nouveau drivers, "
"which are included. However support for this must be manually enabled right "
"now, and is not recommended for non-experts. Follow [the "
"instructions](/docs/pre-turing-nvidia), and temper your expectations "
"accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:167
msgid ""
"I’m a KDE developer. Why should I use KDE Linux, and how does KDE "
"development work?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:168
msgid ""
"KDE Linux is an excellent development platform for KDE software. Advantages "
"over other many distros include:"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:170
msgid ""
"**Faster:** Don’t need to build all dependencies, only the specific thing "
"you’re working on. More speed, less electricity usage and heat generation."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:171
msgid ""
"**Safer:** Compiling into a systemd extension overlaid on top of `/usr` or "
"rolling back to one of the last 5 OS images cached on disk provide multiple "
"easy methods to roll back broken changes."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:172
msgid ""
"**Smaller:** Over 45 GB of space savings compared to a dev setup where you "
"build everything from source."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:173
msgid ""
"**More deterministic:** Build KDE software exactly the way it’s built on KDE"
" Linux or Flathub. No weird bugs from different development toolchains."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:175
msgid "Learn more about [using KDE Linux as a KDE developer](/docs/kde-dev)."
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:178
msgid "This is so cool; how can I get involved with development?"
msgstr ""

#: content/_index.md:179
msgid ""
"Help is always appreciated! You can talk with the KDE Linux developers on "
"[Matrix](https://matrix.to/#/#kde-linux:kde.org), and submit issues or merge"
" requests on [invent.kde.org](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/)."
msgstr ""

